# JARVIS DESIGN SYSTEM RULES

## Core Architecture
- **ITCSS Hierarchy:** Follow Tokens > Base > Objects > Components > Utilities.
- **Layout Sync:** The `main-area` top margin and `sidebar` top position must ALWAYS match `var(--header-height)`.

## Coding Standards (Strict)
- **No Magic Numbers:** Never use raw pixels (e.g., `12px`). You MUST use tokens (e.g., `var(--space-m)`).
- **Z-Index:** Never use integers. Use tokens from `src/css/tokens/z-index.css` (e.g., `var(--z-header)`).
- **Preservation:** When editing a file, do NOT delete existing variants or classes unless explicitly asked.

## Visual Identity
- **Style:** Minimalist, High-Contrast, Professional Tech (Audi-inspired).
- **Colors:** Use `var(--color-brand-black)` for backgrounds and `var(--color-accent)` for interactions.